ComicInfo.Summary: This is part 2 of the three-part storyline, "Darkgods Rampage". As Astron, Astra and Commando D explore the open dimensional rift, and Firebeam exstiguishes the wildfires consuming Miami, The Black Shroud , in his human guise of Kuromoko, revels in his successes, as his evil converts more of Earth's paranormals to his side. She-Cat breaks into Dr. Weir's asylum, only to find it, too overrun with evil dopplegangers- as is The Colorado Project. And Synn is still insistant, she will not leave her room-even when it's a cell at Doc Weir's. Stardust and Ms. Victory bisect the entire globe via The Well Of Souls, only to find more villains waiting for them when they emerge on the other side. The Old Dark Gods are at the dimensional gate- can anything stop them? Written by Bill Black, drawn by Brad Gorby and inked by Mark Heike. Guest starring General Strock, Keela Sentry, Verdon Fell, Carbonator, Iron Jaw, Atoman, Cap'n Joel, General Gordon, Speedbolt, Beamer, Singapore Sal and Frightenstein. Then, Yankee Girl is back, attempting to orient herself to the modern world. Improving herself with some college courses seems like a good idea, until one of her wacky professors turns out to be an old supervillain with a plan to use YG's blood to create a gang of superwomen to do his bidding, in "The School For Yankee Girls", written by Bill Black, pencils by Chris Allen and inks by Mark Heike. It guest stars Kitten, Jetgirl and The Vulture. Color cover by Brad Gorby and Mark Heike, interiors are black and white with graytones. Standard comic book format.
ComicInfo.Title: The School For Yankee Girls; Dark Gods: Rampage (part 2)
